In [10]:
m = folium.Map(location=[vkusvill[""].mean(), vkusvill[""].mean()], zoom_start=10)
marker_cluster = MarkerCluster().add_to(m)
heat_data = []
for idx, row in vkusvill.iterrows():
    location = [row[""], row[""]]
    heat_data.append([row[""], row[""], row[" /"]])
    
    folium.Marker(
        location,
        popup=f"""
        <i> : </i><br><b>{row[' , 2']} 2</b> <br> 
        <i>: </i><b><br>{row['']}</b><br>
        <i>: </i><b><br>{round(row[' /'], 2)}</b><br>
        <i>: </i><b><br>{round(row[' /'], 2)}</b><br>""", 
        ).add_to(marker_cluster)
    
HeatMap(heat_data, radius=18, gradient={0.4: 'blue', 0.65: 'lime', 1: 'red'}).add_to(m)
colormap = folium.branca.colormap.LinearColormap(['blue', 'lime', 'red'], 
                                          vmin=vkusvill[' /'].min(), 
                                          vmax=vkusvill[' /'].max(),
                                          caption=' /')
colormap.add_to(m)
m

In [11]:
def bar_plot(
        column: str, 
        rows: int, 
        cols: int, 
        title: str, 
        width: int,
        height: int,
        xaxes: bool = True
        ):
    
    fig = make_subplots(rows=rows, cols=cols)

    data = vkusvill.groupby([column]).agg(
        {
            '': ['count'],
            ' /': ['mean'],
            ' /': ['mean']
            }
            ).reset_index()
    data.sort_values(column, inplace=True)
    data.columns = data.columns.droplevel(1)

    if rows <= cols:
        fig.add_bar(x=data[column], y=data[""], row=1, col=1)
        fig.add_bar(x=data[column], y=data[" /"], row=1, col=2)
        fig.add_bar(x=data[column], y=data[" /"], row=1, col=3)

        if xaxes:
            fig.update_xaxes(title_text=column, row=1, col=1, title_standoff=1, title_font_size=12)
            fig.update_xaxes(title_text=column, row=1, col=2, title_standoff=1, title_font_size=12)
            fig.update_xaxes(title_text=column, row=1, col=3, title_standoff=1, title_font_size=12)

        fig.update_yaxes(title_text=" ", row=1, col=1, title_standoff=1, title_font_size=12)
        fig.update_yaxes(title_text=" ", row=1, col=2, title_standoff=1, title_font_size=12)
        fig.update_yaxes(title_text="  ", row=1, col=3, title_standoff=1, title_font_size=12)

    else:
        fig.add_bar(x=data[column], y=data[""], row=1, col=1)
        fig.add_bar(x=data[column], y=data[" /"], row=2, col=1)
        fig.add_bar(x=data[column], y=data[" /"], row=3, col=1)

        if xaxes:
            fig.update_xaxes(title_text=column, row=1, col=1, title_standoff=1, title_font_size=12)
            fig.update_xaxes(title_text=column, row=2, col=1, title_standoff=1, title_font_size=12)
            fig.update_xaxes(title_text=column, row=3, col=1, title_standoff=1, title_font_size=12)

        fig.update_yaxes(title_text=" ", row=1, col=1, title_standoff=1, title_font_size=12)
        fig.update_yaxes(title_text=" ", row=2, col=1, title_standoff=1, title_font_size=12)
        fig.update_yaxes(title_text="  ", row=3, col=1, title_standoff=1, title_font_size=12)

    fig.update_layout(
        showlegend=False, 
        title={"text": title, "x": 0.5},
        autosize=False,
        width=width,
        height=height,
        )
    fig.show()
